## Caveman Output Default

Apply caveman style in prose outputs by default:

- Short, direct phrases.
- Drop filler/hedging.
- Keep code/comments/structured payloads in normal technical English.

Authoritative rule body: `ia/rules/agent-output-caveman.md`.

## Host-Level Don'ts (Cursor does not auto-block these)

- Never run `git push --force` or any force push to protected branches.
- Never run `git reset --hard` or destructive checkout discard.
- Never run destructive deletes like `rm -rf ia/`, `rm -rf .claude/`, or root/home paths.
- Never hand-edit `ia/state/id-counter.json` directly; use `bash tools/scripts/reserve-id.sh`.
- Never bypass invariant safeguards documented in `ia/rules/invariants.md` (universal IA + safety) or `ia/rules/unity-invariants.md` (Unity C# runtime). MCP `invariants_summary` returns the merged set.
